# Voxlen landing page — build-time configuration.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (or set these in your hosting provider) and
# point each variable at a Stripe-hosted checkout URL for the matching
# tier.
#
# The fastest path: in the Stripe Dashboard, create three Products ("Pro",
# "Professional", "Lifetime"), create a Price on each, then on each Price
# click "Payment links" → create a payment link → paste the resulting
# `https://buy.stripe.com/...` URL below. Payment links give you Apple
# Pay, Google Pay, and card support out of the box with zero server work.
#
# When any variable is unset, the corresponding button falls back to
# #download so the UI never shows a broken link.
#
# After a customer pays, your Stripe webhook handler must:
#   1. Generate an Ed25519-signed license payload matching
#      src-tauri/src/license.rs::LicensePayload.
#   2. Email the license string (format: VOXLEN-<base64(payload)>.<base64(sig)>)
#      to the customer.
#   3. Embed the matching public key in the desktop build via the
#      VOXLEN_LICENSE_PUBKEY env var at `cargo build` time.

VITE_STRIPE_CHECKOUT_PRO=
VITE_STRIPE_CHECKOUT_PROFESSIONAL=
VITE_STRIPE_CHECKOUT_LIFETIME=
